《'''餓鬼：毛時代大饑荒揭秘'''》(''Hungry Ghosts: Mao's Secret Famine'')<ref>{{cite book|author=Jasper Becker|title=Hungry Ghosts: Mao's Secret Famine|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=3VeLKJyRzuQC|date=15 April 1998|publisher=Henry Holt and Company|isbn=978-0-8050-5668-6}}</ref>是由《[[南華早報|南華早報]]》駐北京記者站主任{{le|賈斯柏·貝克|Jasper Becker}}寫的一本書。中譯本由姜和平翻譯，[[明鏡出版社|明鏡出版社]]出版。<ref name="貝克">{{cite book | author=賈斯柏‧貝克 | others=姜和平 譯 |
title=餓鬼：毛時代大饑荒揭秘 |
publisher=明鏡出版社 |
date=2005年10月 |
url=http://books.google.com/books?id=hjpdAAAAIAAJ |
isbn=978-1-932138-30-6}}</ref>本書詳細描述了[[毛澤東|毛澤東]]的[[大躍進|大躍進]]所造成的[[三年困難時期|大饑荒]]。本書曾獲荷蘭PIOOM人權獎。<ref name="Becker2000">{{cite book|author=Jasper Becker|title=The Chinese|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=bG2EpQDm9UUC|year=2000|publisher=Free Press|isbn=978-0-684-84412-1 | quote=His Hungry Ghosts was the winner of the Dutch PIOOM award for human rights.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.broadbook.com/1product.asp?id=244 | title=餓鬼：毛時代大饑荒揭秘 | publisher=博大書局 | access-date=2013-11-20 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150610220149/http://www.broadbook.com/1product.asp?id=244 | archive-date=2015-06-10 | dead-url=no }}</ref>

對於大饑荒造成的死亡人數，[[中國經濟體制改革研究所|中國經濟體制改革研究所]]所長[[陳一諮|陳一諮]]表示，該所根據[[中國共產黨|中國共產黨]]黨內文件所寫成的秘密報告，認為饑荒死亡數是4300万-4500万。另一份提供中央領導參閲的資料認為人數達5、6千萬。<ref name="Becker1998">{{cite book|author=Jasper Becker|title=Hungry Ghosts: Mao's Secret Famine|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=3VeLKJyRzuQC&pg=271|date=15 April 1998|publisher=Henry Holt and Company|isbn=978-0-8050-5668-6|pages=271–272|access-date=2013-11-20|archive-date=2015-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150319214623/http://books.google.com/books?id=3VeLKJyRzuQC&pg=271|dead-url=no}}</ref>

貝克指出，如果不是毛澤東長時間否認危機的存在，食物嚴重短缺和饑荒是可以避免的。1949年後，共產黨完全壟斷中國輿論工具。在中國的言論沈默期間，西方觀察家的作用變得重要。[[西方媒體|西方媒體]]向世界披露了中國的實情，但當大躍進成為可怕的悲劇時，[[左派|左派]]觀察家如[[埃德加·斯諾|埃德加·斯諾]]、[[路易·艾黎|路易·艾黎]]和[[安娜·路易絲·斯特朗|安娜·路易絲·斯特朗]]保持沉默或淡化它的嚴重性。<ref name="貝克"/>{{rp|419-429}}

貝克結論，如果中共高官敢與毛澤東爭論，第一年後悲劇本來是可以避免的。<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.amazon.com/Hungry-Ghosts-Secret-Famine-Paperback/dp/0805056688 | title=Hungry Ghosts: Mao's Secret Famine (Holt Paperback) | quote=The tragedy could have been averted, Becker concludes, after the first year if Mao's senior advisers had dared to confront him. | website=Amazon.com | publisher=Library Journals LLC | author=Jack Shreve | access-date=2017-05-18 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170709002634/https://www.amazon.com/Hungry-Ghosts-Secret-Famine-Paperback/dp/0805056688 | archive-date=2017-07-09 | dead-url=no }}{{en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://bepl.ent.sirsi.net/client/en_US/default/search/detailnonmodal/ent:$002f$002fSD_ILS$002f0$002fSD_ILS:924510/ada | title=Hungry ghosts : Mao's secret famine | year=2010 | publisher=Library Journals LLC | access-date=2017-05-18 | archive-date=2019-06-15 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190615213328/https://bepl.ent.sirsi.net/client/en_US/default/search/detailnonmodal/ent:$002f$002fSD_ILS$002f0$002fSD_ILS:924510/ada | dead-url=no }}{{en}}</ref>

